label.value: positive regulation of transmembrane receptor protein serine/threonine kinase signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a transmembrane receptor serine/threonine kinase binding to its physiological ligand.

label.value: negative regulation of transmembrane receptor protein serine/threonine kinase signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a transmembrane receptor serine/threonine kinase binding to its physiological ligand.

label.value: tissue migration

value.value: The process in which the population of cells that make up a tissue undergo directed movement.

label.value: epithelium migration

value.value: The process in which the population of cells that make up an epithelium undergo directed movement.

label.value: membrane fission

value.value: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the separation of a single continuous membrane into two membranes.

label.value: establishment of protein localization to membrane

value.value: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location in a membrane.

label.value: establishment of epithelial cell polarity

value.value: The specification and formation of anisotropic intracellular organization of an epithelial cell.

label.value: establishment of epithelial cell planar polarity

value.value: The specification and formation of the polarity of an epithelial cell along the plane of the epithelial tissue.

label.value: Golgi disassembly

value.value: A cellular process that results in the breakdown of a Golgi apparatus that contributes to Golgi inheritance.

label.value: Golgi reassembly

value.value: The reformation of the Golgi following its breakdown and partitioning contributing to Golgi inheritance.

label.value: regulation of spindle assembly

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of spindle assembly. Spindle assembly is the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the spindle, the array of microtubules and associated molecules that serves to move duplicated chromosomes apart.

label.value: regulation of Golgi inheritance

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of Golgi inheritance. Golgi inheritance is the partitioning of Golgi apparatus between daughter cells at cell division.

label.value: chondrocyte morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the structures of a chondrocyte are generated and organized. This process occurs while the initially relatively unspecialized cell is acquiring the specialized features of a chondrocyte.

label.value: organelle membrane fusion

value.value: The joining of two lipid bilayers to form a single organelle membrane.

label.value: regulation of establishment of planar polarity

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the establishment of planar polarity, the coordinated organization of groups of cells in a tissue, such that they all orient to similar coordinates.

label.value: microtubule cytoskeleton organization involved in establishment of planar polarity

value.value: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising microtubules and their associated proteins and contributes to the establishment of planar polarity.

label.value: establishment of planar polarity involved in neural tube closure

value.value: Coordinated organization of groups of cells in the plane of an epithelium that contributes to the closure of the neural tube.

label.value: regulation of establishment of planar polarity involved in neural tube closure

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the establishment of planar polarity involved in neural tube closure, the coordinated organization of groups of cells in the plane of an epithelium that contributes to the closure of the neural tube.

label.value: planar cell polarity pathway involved in neural tube closure

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by binding of a Wnt protein to a receptor on the surface of the target cell where activated receptors signal via downstream effectors that modulates the establishment of planar polarity contributing to neural tube closure.

label.value: regulation of cholesterol metabolic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of cholesterol metabolism, the chemical reactions and pathways involving cholesterol, cholest-5-en-3 beta-ol, the principal sterol of vertebrates and the precursor of many steroids, including bile acids and steroid hormones.

label.value: positive regulation of cholesterol metabolic process

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of cholesterol metabolism, the chemical reactions and pathways involving cholesterol, cholest-5-en-3 beta-ol, the principal sterol of vertebrates and the precursor of many steroids, including bile acids and steroid hormones.

label.value: negative regulation of cholesterol metabolic process

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of cholesterol metabolism, the chemical reactions and pathways involving cholesterol, cholest-5-en-3 beta-ol, the principal sterol of vertebrates and the precursor of many steroids, including bile acids and steroid hormones.

label.value: regulation of spindle organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the microtubule spindle.

label.value: fibroblast growth factor receptor signaling pathway involved in somitogenesis

value.value: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a fibroblast growth factor receptor binding to one of its physiological ligands that contributes to somitogenesis.

label.value: Wnt signaling pathway involved in somitogenesis

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by binding of Wnt protein to a frizzled family receptor on the surface of the target cell and ending with a change in cell state that contributes to somitogenesis.

label.value: axis elongation involved in somitogenesis

value.value: The developmental growth that results in the elongation of the rostral-caudal axis that contributes to somitogenesis.

label.value: convergent extension involved in somitogenesis

value.value: The morphogenetic process in which a presomitic mesoderm narrows along the left-right axis and lengthens in the rostral-caudal axis contributing to somitogenesis.

label.value: cell migration involved in somitogenic axis elongation

value.value: Any process involved in the controlled self-propelled movement of a cell that contributes to somitogenic axis elongation.

label.value: regulation of cell migration involved in somitogenic axis elongation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the controlled self-propelled movement of a cell that contributes to somitogenic axis elongation.

label.value: protein localization involved in establishment of planar polarity

value.value: Any process in which a protein is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location in a cell that contributes to the establishment of planar polarity.

label.value: regulation of muscle system process

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a muscle system process, a multicellular organismal process carried out by any of the organs or tissues in a muscle system.

label.value: positive regulation of canonical Wnt signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the Wnt signaling pathway through beta-catenin, the series of molecular signals initiated by binding of a Wnt protein to a frizzled family receptor on the surface of the target cell, followed by propagation of the signal via beta-catenin, and ending with a change in transcription of target genes.

label.value: regulation of somatostatin secretion

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, extent of the regulated release of somatostatin from secretory granules in the D cells of the pancreas.

label.value: positive regulation of somatostatin secretion

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, extent of the regulated release of somatostatin from secretory granules in the D cells of the pancreas.

label.value: negative regulation of somatostatin secretion

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, extent of the regulated release of somatostatin from secretory granules in the D cells of the pancreas.

label.value: regulation of peptide hormone secretion

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the regulated release of a peptide hormone from secretory granules.

label.value: positive regulation of peptide hormone secretion

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the regulated release of a peptide hormone from secretory granules.

label.value: negative regulation of peptide hormone secretion

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the regulated release of a peptide hormone from secretory granules.

label.value: regulation of cellular response to growth factor stimulus

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a growth factor stimulus.

label.value: negative regulation of cellular response to growth factor stimulus

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a growth factor stimulus.

label.value: regulation of neural crest formation

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of neural crest formation. Neural crest formation is the formation of the specialized region of ectoderm between the neural ectoderm (neural plate) and non-neural ectoderm. The neural crest gives rise to the neural crest cells that migrate away from this region as neural tube formation proceeds.

label.value: positive regulation of neural crest formation

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of neural crest formation. Neural crest formation is the formation of the specialized region of ectoderm between the neural ectoderm (neural plate) and non-neural ectoderm. The neural crest gives rise to the neural crest cells that migrate away from this region as neural tube formation procedes.

label.value: negative regulation of neural crest formation

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of neural crest formation. Neural crest formation is the formation of the specialized region of ectoderm between the neural ectoderm (neural plate) and non-neural ectoderm. The neural crest gives rise to the neural crest cells that migrate away from this region as neural tube formation procedes.

label.value: positive regulation of wound healing

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the series of events that restore integrity to a damaged tissue, following an injury.

label.value: nucleic acid metabolic process

value.value: Any cellular metabolic process involving nucleic acids.

definition.value: This term should not be used for direct annotation. It should be possible to make a more specific annotation to one of the children of this term.

label.value: meiotic spindle assembly

value.value: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the spindle that contributes to the process of meiosis.

label.value: mitotic spindle assembly

value.value: Mitotic bipolar spindle assembly begins with spindle microtubule nucleation from the separated spindle pole body, includes spindle elongation during prometaphase, and is complete when all kinetochores are stably attached the spindle, and the spindle assembly checkpoint is satisfied.

label.value: positive regulation of intracellular protein transport

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of proteins within cells.

label.value: negative regulation of intracellular protein transport

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of proteins within cells.

label.value: regulation of locomotion involved in locomotory behavior

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the self-propelled movement of a cell or organism from one location to another in a behavioral context; the aspect of locomotory behavior having to do with movement.
